---
description: After editing Justin_Study_Agent (school-courses-review) or Firebase config, deploy and push
globs: school-courses-review/**,firebase.json,.firebaserc,package.json,package-lock.json,.github/workflows/**
alwaysApply: false
---

When you change `school-courses-review/`, `firebase.json`, `.firebaserc`, or `package.json`:

1. From project root `d:\Cursor_Projects\Justin_School_Course`, run `npm.cmd run deploy:all` (Hosting + Cloud Functions). Use `deploy:hosting` or `deploy:functions` if you only changed one side. Requires Firebase CLI login; Functions need Blaze plan and Secret `GEMINI_API_KEY` (see `DEPLOY.md`).
2. Commit and push to `origin main` for the changed files. Do **not** commit `Chapter 6.pdf`, `.firebase/`, or `node_modules/`.
3. If GitHub Actions secret `FIREBASE_TOKEN` is set, pushing to `main` also deploys hosting automatically—local `firebase deploy` is still optional for instant verification.
